href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>When a <fr:link
href="jms-001S.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-001S">pointed</fr:link> dcpo <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> satisfies either of the following equivalent conditions, we will refer to it as <fr:em>positively generated</fr:em>.</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li>Every element <fr:tex>a: A</fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="jms-002F.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-002F">positively generated</fr:link>, i.e. we have <fr:tex>a =  \bigsqcup _{p: \mathsf { pos } \, a}a</fr:tex>.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>For any semidirected subset <fr:tex>I \subseteq  A</fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex>\bigsqcup  I =  \bigsqcup   { \mathopen {} \left \{ a \in  I  \mid   \mathsf { pos } \, a \right \} \mathclose {}}</fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol>
 
   
   <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>13798</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:addr>#515</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-515.xml</fr:route><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>16</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-0023</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:p>(2) implies (1) by setting <fr:tex>I =  { \mathopen {} \left \{ a \right \} \mathclose {}}</fr:tex>. Conversely, assume that each element is the supremum of its positive part and fix a semidirected subset <fr:tex>I \subseteq  A</fr:tex>. We compute:</fr:p>

  <fr:tex
display="block">\bigsqcup { \mathopen {} \left \{ a  \in  I  \mid   \mathsf { pos } \, a \right \} \mathclose {}}    =    \bigsqcup _{a \in   { \mathopen {} \left \{ a  \in  I \mid   \mathsf { pos } \, a \right \} \mathclose {}} }a   =    \bigsqcup _{a \in  I} \bigsqcup _{p \in   \mathsf { pos } \, a} a   =    \bigsqcup _{a \in  I} a   </fr:tex>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
